# Multi-direction routes

When a route has more than one travel direction (e.g. southbound / northbound):

- Set `number` to the in-game route number only (`25`, not `25N`).
- Add one `stops[]` entry per direction with `directionKey` (`N`, `S`, `E`, `W`), bilingual `direction`, and ordered `list`.
- UI toggles appear automatically when `stops.length > 1` (card + detail); Chinese locales show 北行/南行, others show N/S. Sort order: N before S, W before E.
- Per-direction `serviceTime` on each `stops[]` entry (departure point only); never combine both terminuses at route level.
- Endpoints on card/detail come from the active direction’s first/last stop; detail shows endpoints once only.
- Single-direction or circular routes: one `stops` entry only (see route 21A).
- **Loop with east/west (or north/south) legs:** keep `pattern: 'circular'` and add `loop` service type; still use multiple `stops[]` entries with `directionKey` `E`/`W` (see route `246X`, in-game loop code `246XA`).

Follow the worked example: route `25` in `src/data/routes.ts`.
